char->functions

primer, ch.11

defined in <ctype.h>
can't be applied to a string as a whole, but to the individual chars in a string

(1) toupper() capitalizes a char given as arg

EXAMPLE
(1)
include <ctype.h>

char s[] = "joe doe";
toupper_s(s);
printf("%s", s); // JOE DOE

void toupper_s(char *s) {
    while (*s) { // exit: \0 == 0 (false)
        *s = toupper(*s); // from <ctype.h>
        s++;
    }
}
